Heartbeat, HeartbeatPipe, Pipe<I2,I2>, Node, Sink<I2>, Source<I2>, MetaDataManageable<Object,Object>, MetaDataProvider<CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>>
public class TimeStampIdentityPipe<I,I2 extends TimeStampedObject<I>>
extends AbstractTimeStampPipe<I,I,I2,I2>

Operator component in a query graph that performs the identity operation. All elements are directly transferred to this pipe's subscribed sinks. Due to extension of AbstratTimeStampPipe, timestamp information are available.

Method Detail

processObject

public void processObject(I2 o,
                          int sourceID)
                   throws IllegalArgumentException
Description copied from class: AbstractPipe
This method has to be overwritten to process each incoming element. The transfer method has to be called inside this method to transfer the processing results to all subscribed sinks. Consequently, its execution is considered to be atomar.

Specified by:
processObject in class AbstractPipe<I2 extends TimeStampedObject<I>,I2 extends TimeStampedObject<I>>
Parameters:
o - The element streaming in.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - If the given element or ID is incorrect.
